cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the problem of mapping relational databases to RDF and OWL, which is a fundamental problem in the development of the Semantic Web. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), as the paper deals with ontology and semantics. The paper also discusses the properties of the mapping, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
